    "question": "Which requirement flow-down views are defined for the APS Black Box Specification?",
    "durationMs": 76118,
    "status": "OK",
    "finalAnswer": "The APS Black Box Specification defines the following 12 requirement flow-down views:\n\n1. APS Interface Requirements\n2. APS Environmental Requirements\n3. APS Programmatic Requirements\n4. APS Architecture Requirements\n5. APS Performance Requirements\n6. APS Timing Requirements\n7. APS Software Requirements\n8. APS Product Assurance Requirements\n9. APS Operational Requirements\n10. APS Optical Requirements\n11. CAGS Driven Requirements\n12. ICD Requirements\n\nThese views are organized under the package \"02 Requirements Flow-down Views\" within the APS Black Box Specification structure.",
    "error": null,
